<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06215054 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06215054 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  MUSIC; MOVIE; CELEBRITY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  MICHAEL Jackson's first film project under his rich deal with Sony will beColumbia Pictures' futuristic action-fantasy feature &quot;Midknight,&quot; which JonPeters is likely to produce, sources said.;    The long-in-developmentproject, known only as &quot;The Michael Jackson Project,&quot; was penned by CarolineThompson and Larry Wilson (&quot;The Addams Family&quot;). Academy Award-winning setdesigner Anton Furst (&quot;Batman&quot;) will produce as well as design the sets.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Eye  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JACKSON FILM SOUNDS LIKE A THRILLER  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  MOVIES  </MEMO><TEXT>     A major event;    In the film, Jackson's character has the ability to beall-powerful and all-knowing -- a power that leaves him open to exploitationby a doctor who tries to use the young man's powers toward his own evil goals.But Jackson's character manages to break away and use his powers against thedoctor.;    An insider close to the project, who requested anonymity, said,&quot;Things will be done in this movie that have never been done before. It willbe a major-event picture in the near future.&quot;;    No director is set yet and astart date is uncertain pending the receipt of the final draft of the film andJackson's schedule. However, one source said he thought the movie would beginfilming in mid-1992.;    Album is late;    The release of Jackson'smuch-anticipated album &quot;Dangerous&quot; has missed delivery for its July 15 windowand will likely miss its Sept. 15 backup release date. Sony Records officialshave said the album definitely will be released this year. There have beenrumors of a 1992-93 world tour, though Jackson said at the end of his lasttour that he would not go on the road again.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Hollywood Reporter  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910802  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  14  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  268  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday August 2, 199100215054,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>